cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with social tagging systems and their semantic stability. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it discusses the description of resources on the web. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it explores the properties of natural language in social tagging systems. The paper also touches upon the topic of shared background knowledge, which could place it under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it discusses the factors that can explain semantic stabilization in social tagging systems.
